                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="12935300" author="heshan" created="Wed, 24 Nov 2010 11:44:23 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I will provide a fix for this issue. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12935301" author="heshan" created="Wed, 24 Nov 2010 11:53:51 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;In the AbstractSynapseArtifactDeployer&apos;s undeploy() method we are removing the artifacts from the SynapseArtifactDeploymentStore, assuming that it is a hot update. But it should remove these artifacts if it is not a restored file. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The attached fix resolves this issue. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12935303" author="heshan" created="Wed, 24 Nov 2010 12:08:12 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;While fixing this issue, I came across another issue.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In the SynapseArtifactDeploymentStore, we are having a Map which Keeps track of the deployed artifacts in the synapse environment named fileName2ArtifactName. It is defined as a static variable. IMV this should not be a static variable.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The other Map which Keeps track of the updating artifacts in the synapse environment in a particular instance, is not defined in the static scope. I think it is the correct way. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Therefore re-attaching the patch with the proposed fix. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12935658" author="supun" created="Thu, 25 Nov 2010 06:37:17 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Applied the patch. Thanks Heshan for the contribution.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
